IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
On November 9, 2023, at approximately 1159 hours, I, Trooper Williams of the Maryland State Police assigned to the North East Barrack was dispatched for deceased person call for service. I arrived on scene located at 1 Renee Carr Street, Elkton, Cecil County, Maryland. I made contact with the caller who identified himself as Jesse Sunderland, DOB: 07/31/1984, W/M, address: 1 Renee Carr Street, Elkton, MD, phone number: 443-206-3474. EMS was on scene prior to my arrival.
                Mr. Sunderland advised he was getting ready to check on his sister-in-law when he observed her body was slumped over on the bed. Mr. Sunderland advised he called 911 requesting an ambulance. Mr. Sunderland identified the deceased female as Brandy Alley, DOB: 12/16/1974, W/F, address: 1 Renee Carr St, Elkton, MD. Mr. Sunderland advised he discovered Ms. Alley at approximately 11:38 hours on November 9, 2023. I made entry into the residence and followed EMS to the back bedroom. I observed Ms. Alley’s body sitting on the bed both legs crossed leaning to the right toward the wall, with a blanket wrapped around the mid-section. I did not observe any signs of foul play. I made contact with Ms. Alley’s sister who identified herself as Crista Sunderland, DOB: 04/27/1970, W/F, address: 1 Renee Carr St, Elkton, MD.
                Mrs. Sunderland advised that Ms. Alley had been dealing with depression for three years due to the passing of their mother. Mrs. Sunderland advised that over the last few weeks the depression happened to get worse. Mrs. Sunderland advised Ms. Alley had a medical history of Down syndrome and was being treated by Dr. Shahnawaz Kahn who has a private practice located at 2533 Augustine Herman Highway Suite A., Chesapeake City, Maryland contact number 410-885-5018. The EMS unit that was on scene identified himself as Kevin McMinn EMS2 and provided the incident number 2314328. McMinn advised Ms. Alley succumbed to Cardiac Arrest. Mr. McMinn advised based on the condition of the body and lack of mobility Ms. Alley had been deceased for several hours.
                I spoke with Mrs. Sunderland and advised her to contact Ms. Alley’s doctor named to determine if he would sign the death certificate. Dr. Kahn advised he would sign the document. Mr. Sunderland contacted the Crouch funeral home. The representative gave an ETA of 45 minutes. Crouch arrived on scene at approximately 1352 hours. Crouch funeral home removed the deceased from the residence.

I request this case be closed.
All event’s occurred in Cecil County, Maryland.
